  "prompt": "What are the vacations in IITs?",
  "response": "Indian Institutes of Technology (IITs) generally have structured academic calendars that include breaks and vacations. However, specific vacation periods can vary slightly from one IIT to another. Here are some common vacation periods in most IITs:\n\n1. **Winter Break**: Typically, a short winter break is scheduled around late December to early January. This break usually lasts for around two to three weeks.\n\n2. **Summer Vacation**: The longest break is the summer vacation, which generally starts in May and lasts till late July or early August. This is after the end of the spring semester and before the start of the fall semester. It usually lasts for about two to three months.\n\n3. **Mid-Semester Breaks**: Some IITs may have a short mid-semester break in each semester, allowing students a few days off from classes.\n\n4. **National Holidays**: IITs also observe national holidays such as Diwali, Holi, Independence Day, Republic Day, and other regional or religious holidays.\n\n5. **Semester Breaks**: At the end of each semester, there's usually a brief inter-semester break of one to two weeks before the next semester begins.\n\nFor the exact dates and duration of these breaks, it is best to refer to the specific academic calendar of the respective IITs. Each IIT publishes its academic schedule, which includes detailed information about semester duration, examination periods, and vacation dates.",
